The paper deals with approximation algorithms for optimization problems on geometric intersection graphs, specifically unit disk graphs. This falls under computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of shifting coresets, which is a technique commonly used in data stream algorithms (cs.DM) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper presents results for well-known optimization problems, which may be of interest to researchers in theoretical computer science (cs.GT).
